        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3911755" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15062917815143352054">fanon takes psychoanalysis, phenomenology, and his incredible mind and goes amazing places; evades being bogged down by psychoanalytic dogma, while using its concepts to tease out a living constellation of power relations and problems of race and representation. so apt and agile and fascinating that it gets my 5 stars despite its raging sexism, ablism, homophobia. <br/><br/>The first lines are just stunning. <br/><br/> &quot;The explosion will not happen today. It is too soon... or too late. <br/> I did not come with timeles</span>
  <span id="freeText15062917815143352054" style="display:none">fanon takes psychoanalysis, phenomenology, and his incredible mind and goes amazing places; evades being bogged down by psychoanalytic dogma, while using its concepts to tease out a living constellation of power relations and problems of race and representation. so apt and agile and fascinating that it gets my 5 stars despite its raging sexism, ablism, homophobia. <br /><br />The first lines are just stunning. <br /><br /> "The explosion will not happen today. It is too soon... or too late. <br /> I did not come with timeless truths.<br /> My consciousenss is not illuminated with ultimate radiances.<br /> Nevertheless, in complete composure, I think it would eb good if certain things were said."<br /></span>
